  "pages": [
    {
      "type": "patchouli:text",
      "text": "With budding blocks in mind you designed the Crystallarieum: an Ink-powered contraption that grows chunks of raw ore into sparkling crystals.$(br)Though your best efforts failed to grow actual $(l:general/shards)gems$(/l), you quickly realised that it could grow all sorts of other resources instead."
    },
    {
      "type": "spectrum:pedestal_crafting",
      "title": "Pedestal Recipe",
      "recipe": "spectrum:pedestal/tier4/crystallarieum",
      "text": "Simply throw raw ore on top to let it crystallize.$(br)Each resource requires one color of Ink. "
    },
    {
      "type": "patchouli:text",
      "title": "Growing Metals",
      "text": "Metallic resources require unrefined materials such as $(item)Raw Iron$(), resulting in a $(item)Small Iron Bud$() that will grow steadily until it reaches maturity and can be safely harvested.$(br)For crystalline blocks, an existing one may be used as a seed."
    },
    {
      "type": "patchouli:text",
      "title": "Catalysts",
      "text": "The Crystallarieum also fits a stack of catalysts, speed up the process, or lower Ink consumption. While catalysts are mostly optional, some special materials may require them."
    },
